## Important Linux Commands

### Check Kernel Version

```bash
uname -r
```

### View PID 1 Process

```bash
ps -p 1
```

### Analyze Boot Time

```bash
systemd-analyze
```

### List Running Services

```bash
systemctl list-units --type=service
```

### View Boot Logs

```bash
journalctl -b
```

